**README.md serves as the primary user-facing documentation for agents-reverse-engineer, explaining installation, workflow, commands, and generated documentation formats with marketing-oriented positioning for AI assistant users.**

## Installation Methods

Describes three installation approaches via `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest`:
- Interactive installer with runtime selection prompts (Claude Code, OpenCode, Gemini CLI, or all)
- Non-interactive with `--runtime <rt>` flag and `-g` (global `~/.claude/`) or `-l` (local `./.claude/`) location flags
- Uninstall via `npx agents-reverse-engineer@latest uninstall` removing command files, session hooks, ARE permissions from settings.json, and `.agents-reverse-engineer` folder (local only)

## Core Workflow Steps

Documents six-step user workflow executed within AI assistant:
1. `/are-init` — Creates `.agents-reverse-engineer/config.yaml` with exclusion patterns
2. `/are-discover` — Scans codebase respecting `.gitignore`, generates `GENERATION-PLAN.md` via post-order traversal (deepest directories first)
3. `/are-generate` — Three-phase execution: file analysis (`.sum` files) → directory docs (`AGENTS.md`) → root docs (`CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, `OPENCODE.md`)
4. `/are-update` — Incremental regeneration for changed files only via hash-based change detection
5. `/are-specify` — Synthesizes all `AGENTS.md` into `specs/SPEC.md` (supports `--multi-file` split and `--dry-run` preview)
6. `/are-clean` — Removes all generated documentation artifacts

## CLI Commands

Lists terminal commands with flags:
- `are` or `are install` — Interactive installer (default)
- `are install --runtime <rt> -g/-l` — Install to runtime globally/locally
- `are install -u` — Uninstall (remove files/hooks)
- `are init` — Create configuration file
- `are discover` — List files for analysis (supports `--plan` for GENERATION-PLAN.md, `--show-excluded` for exclusion reasons)
- `are generate` — Generate all documentation
- `are update` — Update changed files only
- `are specify` — Generate project specification
- `are clean` — Remove all generated docs

Runtime values: `claude`, `opencode`, `gemini`, `all`

